## Make sure you seek routine and emergency care
If people can visit their GP or diabetes support team via telehealth, it is a
great way to keep up with routine checks.
For people with chronic health conditions, like diabetes, it’s essential that
they continue to look after their health. Even during the COVID-19 pandemic
it’s important to seek routine medical care and take action in an emergency.
If you’re experiencing symptoms like shortness of breath, severe fevers or
dehydration you should seek out urgent medical care. Don’t wait as it could
Eating a healthy, well-balanced diet, getting plenty of sleep and including
exercise in your day can help you stay in good health.
Staying on top of your diabetes management routine is also important.
At this time you also need to maintain good hygiene, wash your hands regularly
and practice social distancing. All of these action will protect you from
